			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.homelanfed.com/index.php?id=25837" target="_blank">http://www.homelanfed.com/index.php?id=25837</a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The Sony Online team working on their original fantasy MMORPG Everquest continue to create new original content for the game, even as the much hyped sequel Everquest 2 gets ready for its scheduled lauch this fall. Everquest: Omens of War is the upcoming and latest commerical expansion pack for the game and HomeLAN got its lead designer Shawn Lord and community relations manager Alan Crosby to tell us more about the expansion.
<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - How did the idea behind Omens of War come about?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - We started exploring many of the ideas during Planes of Power. As time progressed, we figured out how to meet the various goals that needed to be set for the expansions, and then we gathered feedback on the story as we progressed to this point. Omens of War is a continuation of several storylines that have been moved into the foreground over the last couple of expansions. It is also the precursor for a slightly different direction in the storyline that will make the path that we've been taking a little more apparent to the people who have been with us for the last 5 years.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - How does the expansion relate to the previous expansion, Gates of Discord?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Omens of War provides an explanation to some of the characters that  were introduced and concepts that were mentioned during Gates. Adventurers will begin to learn more about Discord and its role in the EverQuest universe. As they enter the war-ravished world of Kuua, they'll see the effects it can have on a world similar to theirs. The purpose of offering this sort of environment isn't to sidetrack the adventurers or move them away from Norrath; it's simply an example of what might happen should Norrath fall victim to the same influence.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What kind of new locations and environments will be seen in Omens of War?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Adventurers visit a small section of a world of Kuua. This region of Kuua, an area surrounding the ruined city of Dranik, is a great example of what the various forces that move along the edge of Discord's influence can do to a world... or more appropriately, cause a world to do to itself. This region contains many of our favorite elements - a ruined city, a corrupted palace, lost catacombs, winding gorges, and much more. The zones are some of the most beautiful and complex maps I've seen so far. The artists did an outstanding job.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What kinds of new quests will be given in the new expansion?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Adventurers will be able to quest for many different types of rewards. They'll be able to gain favor with some of the locals, learn about the history of the region and its occupiers, and also earn items of power in the process. This expansion also offers new "Epic" quests for each of the character classes. It's been a few years since we last attempted this sort of content. We've taken care to create the quests in a way that will allow players of varying power levels to earn an item and then increase its power. In effect, if you count the post-Kunark Epic quests as Epic 1.0, we're releasing 1.5 and 2.0 with this expansion. In addition, the new engine has allowed the artists to produce some really amazing looking items.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What kinds of new NPCs and monsters will be encountered in Omens of War?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Adventurers will immediately be greeted by several of Kuua's native races. Giants that have been corrupted, bizarre jellyfish-like creatures, and even a dragon-like race that used to rule over the area. The latter will provide many of the answers to the story of this place. There are also a few familiar non-native creatures in the area. Some of these were introduced during Gates of Discord. These are the remaining elements of Mata Muram's legion. Muram's army is basically a menagerie of villainous races that he's gathered during his enslaving expeditions on each of the worlds that Discord has influenced.
<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What other new and improved gameplay featured will be put into the expansion?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - This expansion also includes the new task system. This is our first attempt to create a system that caters to players who only have 30 - 90 minutes to play and haven't found a group or prefer to play solo for a little while. Adding a completely new way to play the game is a challenge at this point, but we've been really happy with the feedback we've received so far. At ship, we will have task givers in place in each of the starting cities and other areas around Norrath for levels 5-65 at this point. That's yet another feature: this expansion will also allow players to progress from 65 to 70. Of course that means we've had to look at every system that deals with character levels and make changes and improvements. This includes new spells, items, and Alternate Advancement abilities. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What will the new graphical improvements in Omens of War be like?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Honestly, you'll have to see them for yourself to really understand what a difference the new graphics engine makes. Everything from the bump and other mapping on models and environments, to the particle effects, and even the skies and water have been revised and dramatically improved. When I run through Omens, its looks like a different game. This expansion is the first of our expansions to take full advantage of the new engine, but already it's easy to see how this game can remain competitive with other titles for years to come.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - What is the current status of the expansion's progress and when will it be released?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - We're currently in our second week of Beta and we have about three and a half weeks left to go. Testing is going really well since we've had literally dozens of guilds donate their time to help us test and tune during Beta. We launch on September 14th.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - After Omens of War, what does the future hold for the original EverQuest with the sequel getting closer to launch?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - The last five years (our time) have covered the Age of Turmoil, a chaotic period of growth and exploration, which has taken place over roughly a hundred years in Norrathian time. As we move forward, we're looking for new ways to push EverQuest, both in storyline and gameplay. Since we still have many hundreds of years and several "Ages" to work through prior to EverQuest 2's "Age of Destiny", players will be able to have the unique opportunity to explore Norrath's past and present at the same time. While discovering what mysteries the future holds, you'll also be able to unearth the secrets of the past.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
HomeLAN - Finally is there anything else you wish to say about EverQuest: Omens of War?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shawn Lord and Alan Crosby - Everyone has worked really hard to get this expansion out, so we hope you enjoy it. We have plenty left in store for Norrath. Our adventurers aren't the only people who have been growing in power and plotting to take over the world! Stay tuned for more information on what's coming next.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">
